TODO

    Very basic channel and connection level documentation has been added, but a second pass is required.

    Lots more information needs to be added here.

    However, this feels somewhat frustrating documenting this, because channels and connections are effectively *internals*, transparent to the user inside a client or server, in most cases.

    But I think if somebody wants to actually understand the library, they are going to want to understand the implementation. This is open source after all.

    I think the key is to split the documentation into sections:

    API, internals. I think I can section it up like this. Put the socket, connection, channel into the internal section.

    Some information on grouping here: http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/manual/grouping.html

    OK. That's enough for the day. Man this is slow, punishing work =p

